00:12:53,278 --> 00:12:56,119
The first step is gathering and recording data.

245
00:12:56,639 --> 00:12:58,359
This is the information is everywhere thing

246
00:12:58,379 --> 00:12:59,460
that I talked about before.

247
00:13:00,352 --> 00:13:03,634
The second step is organizing and reading that data.

248
00:13:03,974 --> 00:13:04,874
And that's metrics.

249
00:13:04,934 --> 00:13:06,555
That's how you visualize your data.

250
00:13:06,836 --> 00:13:10,258
You create measurements or comparisons of that data

251
00:13:10,598 --> 00:13:11,839
that you've already collected.

252
00:13:12,279 --> 00:13:14,080
And then finally, you analyze.

253
00:13:14,580 --> 00:13:17,642
And this is where you come into the picture as a designer.

254
00:13:18,162 --> 00:13:21,084
You need to understand how to interpret all this information

255
00:13:21,404 --> 00:13:23,826
and then combine it with your instincts

256
00:13:24,166 --> 00:13:25,527
and your design insights.

257
00:13:26,342 --> 00:13:30,947
data, metrics, analytics, it might seem like annoying semantics, but it's really important to

258
00:13:31,007 --> 00:13:37,573
understand each of the terms and their differences in order to apply them correctly. And data is

259
00:13:37,673 --> 00:13:43,079
really important because it's kind of the building block for all of these different pieces. And as I

260
00:13:43,139 --> 00:13:49,365
mentioned, data is just information. Which is great as long as you really understand that

261
00:13:49,385 --> 00:13:50,926
that's all that it is.

262
00:13:52,380 --> 00:13:53,721
So let's start with this study.

263
00:13:53,741 --> 00:13:56,844
It's a poll to show who plays video games.

264
00:13:57,384 --> 00:13:58,065
Simple question.

265
00:13:58,605 --> 00:14:00,667
But the results of this were actually

266
00:14:00,707 --> 00:14:01,708
pretty surprising to me.

267
00:14:02,188 --> 00:14:04,650
Because it skewed a lot older than I thought it would,

268
00:14:04,971 --> 00:14:08,253
with the largest group being college-aged,

269
00:14:08,974 --> 00:14:11,296
and it was more female gamers than male.

270
